    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>A draft of the <a href="http://dl.dropbox.com/u/2015884/syllabi/phil540.pdf">course syllabus</a> is now online. For the first day of class, you should read:</p>

<ul>
<li>Michael Smith's <a href="http://www.oxfordscholarship.com.libproxy.usc.edu/view/10.1093/0195145399.001.0001/acprof-9780195145397">handbook</a> article on <a href="http://www.oxfordscholarship.com.libproxy.usc.edu/view/10.1093/0195145399.001.0001/acprof-9780195145397-chapter-5">Humean Rationality</a>.</li>
<li>Lloyd Humberstone's <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/10.2307/2254119">'Direction of fit'</a>.</li>
</ul>


<p>If you haven't yet, I recommend you also take a look at <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/files/4705/4705-h/4705-h.htm#link2H_4_0075">Section iii of Part III of Book II</a> of Hume's <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/4705"><em>Treatise</em></a>.</p>

<p>I will upload a pdf version of chapter 4 of Smith's <em>The Moral Problem</em> in the next few days. This is not required reading, but is worth taking a look.</p>
